### What is Content Projection?

Content projection (also called transclusion) allows you to pass HTML content from a parent component into a child component using `<ng-content>`. This enables reusable, composable components.

### Basic ng-content

```typescript
// Card component
@Component({
  selector: 'app-card',
  template: `
    <div class="card">
      <ng-content></ng-content>
    </div>
  `,
  standalone: true
})
export class CardComponent { }
```

```html
<!-- Parent usage -->
<app-card>
  <h2>Card Title</h2>
  <p>This content is projected into the card.</p>
</app-card>
```

### Multi-Slot Projection with `select`

Use the `select` attribute to project content into specific slots:

```typescript
@Component({
  selector: 'app-panel',
  template: `
    <div class="panel">
      <div class="panel-header">
        <ng-content select="[panel-header]"></ng-content>
      </div>
      <div class="panel-body">
        <ng-content select="[panel-body]"></ng-content>
      </div>
      <div class="panel-footer">
        <ng-content select="[panel-footer]"></ng-content>
      </div>
    </div>
  `,
  standalone: true
})
export class PanelComponent { }
```

```html
<app-panel>
  <div panel-header>Settings</div>
  <div panel-body>
    <p>Panel content goes here.</p>
  </div>
  <div panel-footer>
    <button>Save</button>
  </div>
</app-panel>
```

### Conditional Projection

You can conditionally show content slots:
```html
<div class="card">
  <div *ngIf="showHeader">
    <ng-content select="[header]"></ng-content>
  </div>
  <ng-content></ng-content>
</div>
```

### @ContentChild and @ContentChildren

Access projected content from the component class:

```typescript
@Component({
  selector: 'app-tabs',
  template: `
    <div class="tabs">
      <button *ngFor="let tab of tabs" (click)="selectTab(tab)">
        {{ tab.title }}
      </button>
      <ng-content></ng-content>
    </div>
  `,
  standalone: true,
  imports: [NgFor]
})
export class TabsComponent implements AfterContentInit {
  @ContentChildren(TabComponent) tabs: QueryList<TabComponent>;

  ngAfterContentInit() {
    // Access projected Tab components
    console.log('Tabs:', this.tabs.toArray());
  }

  selectTab(tab: TabComponent) {
    this.tabs.forEach(t => t.active = false);
    tab.active = true;
  }
}
```

### Content vs View Children

| | @ContentChild / @ContentChildren | @ViewChild / @ViewChildren |
|---|---|---|
| **Scope** | Projected content (via ng-content) | Component's own template |
| **Available** | After ngAfterContentInit | After ngAfterViewInit |
| **Example** | Query elements passed between tags | Query elements defined in the template |

```typescript
@Component({...})
export class ExampleComponent implements AfterViewInit, AfterContentInit {
  @ViewChild('myDiv') myDiv: ElementRef;           // From own template
  @ContentChild(TabComponent) tab: TabComponent;   // From projected content

  ngAfterViewInit() {
    console.log('View child:', this.myDiv);
  }

  ngAfterContentInit() {
    console.log('Content child:', this.tab);
  }
}
```
